docs.snippet: The New Jersey Turnpike Authority voted yesterday to raise the minimum toll to 25 cents from 10 cents. The increase is the first in the 21 years of operation of the toll road. The increase, effective April 15, will affect 49 out of a possible 1,60...
docs.lead_paragraph: The New Jersey Turnpike Authority voted yesterday to raise the minimum toll to 25 cents from 10 cents. The increase is the first in the 21 years of operation of the toll road. The increase, effective April 15, will affect 49 out of a possible 1,600 combinations of trips between various interchanges, where the present tolls are 10, 15 or 20 cents.
